as before the luclin and velious expansion.  I had already stopped selling them when Velious came out so not sure the impact that expansion had on the prices for packs.<br><br>I really hate to do this.  Other tailors will be pissed, Joamn seems to be able to sell his for 100pp, or at least he is auctioning them at that rate.  I have seen this happen with alchemy potions, and armor, cured silk is very hard to sell, with wu's available (another chanter trade boost), banded can barely be sold for more than cost.  One person sells for less and eventually most have to follow suit.  It can be annoying, since the expense of learning trade skills will show less return in the long run as a result.<br><br>I am open to debate.. And probably flames as well.... <p>Lorec <br>Wandering Judge of the Tribunal <br>Excellent Tailor <br>Master Baker <br>Lousy Smith <br>Master Brewer <br>Master  Drunk <br>Aspiring Polyglot <br>Wannabe Alchemist <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/7/02 7:37:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attention Tailors!</span><hr size=1> Two words: Deluxe Toolboxes.<br><br>This may also be begging for flames, but...oh well.<br><br>I'm not sure who would ever pay 100pp for tailored backpacks these days. You can get ten-slot Deluxe Toolboxes that will hold giant items from the gnomes in Iceclad for under 2pp. Basically that means they'd have to be willing to pay 98pp extra for one less weight and the 10% weight reduction.<br><br>There was a time when the &quot;combine&quot; button would get people in trouble and destroy the items if you accidentally hit it, but even that isn't true anymore. They're safe, they're cheap and they're pretty easy to get (assuming you have Velious).<br><br>And if you are that concerned about weight, the tailored large bag is a much more weight-friendly purchase. The backpack weighs 3 for ten slots. While two tailored large bags weigh a total of only 1.2 and give you twelve slots.<br><br>Now don't get me wrong, I am a tailor, and I'd love to make huge money selling backpacks for 80pp profit (or 100pp if I hunt my own bears), but I don't even try to sell backpacks. I feel like a dishonest used car salesman whenever I take that much money from someone for something so unnecessary. And I refuse to pay 20pp to a newbie for a HQ pelt, because I assume that at any moment people will wake up and say &quot;100pp for a backpack??? NO THANKS&quot;.<br><br>But anyway, in answer to the above post...charge whatever you want. Any attempt at organized server-wide price fixing is a waste of energy. If you can't sell them very fast at 100pp, then try to sell them at a lower price. Some tailors may yell at you for undercutting the market, but that's their problem, not yours. It's your stuff and you have the right to sell it for whatever price you want (and buyers have the right to ignore you if they don't like your price).<br><br>That's my thought on the matter, for what it's worth. <p>Grimwyrd Storm<BR>(Lux Aeternam)<BR>31st Human Druid of Karana<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uthessalyathelas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThessalyAthelas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/02 10:40:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Attention Tailors!</span><hr size=1> I was actually getting ready to post something similar, along the lines of &quot;Hey, is anyone out there actually going to bother buying a handmade backpack these days?&quot;<br><br>I mostly blame it on the toolboxes and the traders' satchels... Not other tailors, because before then the price for handmade backpacks had remained steady for a long, long time.<br><br>It sucks that the one reliable source of tailoring income that didn't require a bunch of high-level ingredients has basically been shot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 394<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/02 4:51:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Verant really ..</span><hr size=1> .. needs to upgrade the tailored packs.  Make them weigh about 0.5 and hold giant.  Then they'd be good for inventory expansion -- not quite as high demand as bank (most have fewer than 8 packs in inventory), but it would put the demand back to where it was. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/02 9:48:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Verant really ..</span><hr size=1> I don't mind.<br><br>Of course, I don't kill bears, and I'm not yet good enough to reliably make any backpacks, although I'm in shooting range for them.<br><br>I thought the price on HQ bear pelts is ridiculously inflated, anyway.<br><br>Still, as a weenie myself, I can use the 10% weight reduction.  I've tailored a bunch of belt pouches to reduce weight, but if I could replace those with tailored backpacks, I will.  For people with big, bulging muscles, where weight isn't the pressing issue it is with me. given what else is out there, 100 plat for a backpack seems ridiculous.<br><br>Of course, whether people know about the other containers is a different story.<br><br>Lasgalen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showPrevMessage?topicID=136.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showNextMessage?topicID=136.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=136.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.threadControl?topicID=136.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=136.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm22.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=136.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td><